column1: # SOURCE: Derived from wind_turbines-research.csv and daily_weather_openfield-research.csv
# DESCRIPTION: Daily wind energy output per turbine for small/medium/large distributed-scale turbines

# LOGIC: Wind speed extrapolated from 10m to hub height using power law (alpha=0.14). Power curve: P = P_rated * (v^3 - v_cin^3) / (v_rated^3 - v_cin^3) for v_cin <= v <= v_rated; P_rated for v_rated < v <= v_cout; 0 otherwise. Daily energy = avg_power_kw * 24h.

# ASSUMPTIONS: (1) Power-law wind shear exponent 0.14 for open coastal terrain. (2) Daily avg wind speed applied directly to power curve (no sub-daily Weibull correction â€” underestimates output due to Jensen's inequality on cubic curve). (3) No air density correction for altitude/temperature.
